name: tennis
content:
tennis

noun
 
 
/ˈtenɪs/
 
/ˈtenɪs/
[uncountable]
jump to other results
  1. enlarge image
    a game in which two or four players use rackets to hit a ball backwards and forwards across a net on a specially marked court
    • to play tennis
    • a tennis player/court/ball
    • I met a friend for a quick game of tennis after work.
    • a tennis match/tournament
    • She is a popular figure on the international tennis circuit.
    • He retired from competitive tennis at the age of 34.
    see also court tennis, deck tennis, lawn tennis, real tennis, royal tennis, table tennisTopics Sports: ball and racket sportsa1

(North American English court tennis)
